<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-561-392  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 561 392.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  August 21 1989 n552 p45(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>There's room for multiple test techniques. (Speakout feature)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Turino, John L.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Crucial testability standards are involved as the IEEE's TestTechnology Testability Standards Steering Committee meets Aug 28,1989.andP;  There have been setbacks to the IEEE P1149 StandardTestability Bus, proposed as an 'umbrella standard' in 1986.andP;  Thetestability bus standard sought to lower the cost of acquiring andutilizing automatic testing equipment.andP;  It also sought to forgecloser links between the design stage and the engineering stage ofproduct development.andP;  The goal of any standard should be reductionof the cost of design verification, logic and fault simulation,factory testing and troubleshooting.andP;  The ultimate solution may beto build the testing system into the product.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Computer SocietyIEEE P1149 Test Standard CommitteeProfessional AssociationsStandardsAutomatic Test EquipmentPerformance MeasurementProduct Development.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>